name: 2-cyano-3,6-diiodopyridine

The cyano group is highly electronegative and introduces polarity to the molecule, which may raise the melting point due to increased dipole-dipole interactions. The influence of a cyano group can be estimated to contribute +50 °C to the melting point.
Prediction: The overall predicted melting point for 2-cyano-3,6-diiodopyridine is the sum of the melting point of the base molecule (pyridine) and the estimated contributions of the iodine and cyano functional groups: -42 (base pyridine) + 100 (first iodine) + 100 (second iodine) + 50 (cyano group) = 208 °C
